msgid "A <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base32 class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base32</a> link (which always ends with .b32.i2p) is a hash of a <a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64 class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>Base64</a> destination. For services on the network, the Base64 hash is often mapped to an .i2p domain in the addressbook."
