msgid "B33"
msgstr "B33"

msgid "An address containing an encrypted LeaseSet is informally referred to as a b33 address, an extension of a base32 address with the host's public key and signature type encoded into the address instead of a lookup hash. This address type is required for blinded Leasesets. More information: <a href=https://geti2p.net/spec/b32encrypted class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>B33 Specification</a>"
msgstr "Ňěifreli LeaseSet-i olan bir √ľnvan informallńĪqda b33 √ľnvanńĪ adlandńĪrńĪlńĪr, anbarda yerl…ôŇüdirm…ô haŇüńĪ yerin…ô qoyulmuŇü, hostun a√ßńĪq a√ßar v…ô imza n√∂v√ľ √ľnvanńĪn yerin…ô uzantńĪ olan bir base32 √ľnvanńĪdńĪr. Bu √ľnvan n√∂v√ľ, baŇüńĪmsńĪz LeaseSet-l…ôr √ľ√ß√ľn t…ôl…ôb olunur. ∆ŹtraflńĪ m…ôlumat √ľ√ß√ľn: <a href=https://geti2p.net/spec/b32encrypted class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>B33 Specification</a>"

msgid "BOB"
msgstr "BOB"

msgid "BOB (Basic Open Bridge) is a (now-deprecated) simple application-to-router protocol, superseded by <i>SAM</i>. For more information, see the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/api/bob class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
