msgid "Eepget"
msgstr "Eepget"

msgid "A command-line application supplied with I2P that is used to request URL resources, similar to <a href=https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/ class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>wget</a> or <a href=https://curl.haxx.se/ class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>curl</a>. Eepget is also used internally by the router, for example to reseed from remote hosts. By default, eepget uses the HTTP proxy on <code>127.0.0.1:4444</code>."
