msgid "The I2P Network Protocol (I2NP) manages the routing and mixing of messages between routers, in addition to the transport selection (where more than one is supported) when communicating with a peer. For more information, see the <a href=https://geti2p.net/en/docs/protocol/i2np class='sitelink external' target=_blank rel=noreferrer>online documentation</a>."
