msgid "The process of acquiring router identities, normally via <i>clearnet</i> servers, to ensure your router can communicate and build tunnels with other routers on the network. When a router has no router identities for other peers (usually immediately after installation), the process of reseeding is also referred to as <i>bootstrapping</i>."
